===========================================
IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS
===========================================

NewClient Implementation:
- Uses client.NewClientWithOpts with FromEnv and APIVersionNegotiation
- Pings daemon to verify connectivity
- Returns DaemonConnectionError if unreachable
- Properly wraps Docker Engine client

ImageExists Implementation:
- Validates image name first
- Uses ImageInspectWithRaw for existence check
- Returns (false, nil) for NotFound - NOT an error!
- Returns DaemonConnectionError for actual failures
- Proper error classification

GetImage Implementation:
- Validates image name
- Checks existence first (reuses ImageExists)
- Parses reference using name.ParseReference
- Converts using daemon.Image from go-containerregistry
- Returns ImageNotFoundError for missing images
- Returns ImageConversionError for conversion failures

ValidateImageName Implementation:
- Checks for empty string
- Prevents command injection: ; | & $ ` ( ) < > \
- Returns ValidationError with detailed message
- Security-focused validation

Close Implementation:
- Nil-check before closing
- Closes underlying Docker Engine client
- Returns any cleanup errors

